               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Written at <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glplaces.shtml#London (Greater London, England, United Kingdom),        inhabited place [7011781]"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <geogname normal="London (Greater London, England, United Kingdom),         inhabited place [7011781]">London</geogname>
                     </extref> not later than 
							<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1761"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="176105"
                              certainty="before"
                              era="ce"
                              calendar="gregorian">the beginning of
									May 1761</date>
                     </extref>, 
							based largely on a Latin translation
							of the original poem preserved in the late 13th-century <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Nj√°ls Saga</title>, ch. 157. This untitled Old
							Norse poem is a prophetic account of the Battle of Clontarf, fought on 
							<date normal="10140423" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">Good Friday 1014</date>.
							First published in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1768&amp;text=fsio"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title>
                     </extref> (<date normal="1768" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1768</date>).
						</p>
               </scopecontent>
